insert into public.memory_chunks (id, document_id, chunk_index, chunk_text, token_count, embedding_model, embedding, metadata) values ('0f57663c-1694-5cd6-bf7f-e8f2ec8b80f0', 'f09dff2a-7bee-52d9-9bba-82e2c7eddef8', 0, '- Bootstrap completed on 2026-04-26. Assistant identity is Chappie 🧠, Jarvis-like digital assistant: smart, thoughtful, calm, proactive. User is Темыч / Артём, timezone Moscow (UTC+3), prefers Russian, direct style, and wants an "AI office" that turns vague thoughts into plans/processes/artifacts.
- Google Calendar is connected via Composio and works from this environment. User’s primary calendar is a.sidnevart@gmail.com in Europe/Moscow.
- There is a likely Control UI bug/limitation on OpenClaw 2026.4.23: telegram:* sessions open in dashboard, but sending messages from dashboard into telegram sessions does not work reliably even when gateway auth is fixed. TUI/main/Telegram itself work; issue appears specific to dashboard send flow for telegram sessions.
- OpenClaw Office UI was already installed before changes. Final setup: systemd service `openclaw-office.service` on 127.0.0.1:5180, exposed through nginx at `https://80.74.25.43:8443/office/`, with websocket proxy working.
- For Office UI, gateway token should come from `/opt/openclaw-stack/secrets/gateway-token`; avoid exposing it in process argv or logs.
- Office UI package version in use is old enough that subpath support is not native; `/office/` works via nginx rewrites/sub_filter and may be somewhat fragile. Gateway/Telegram/Composio/web search were intentionally left untouched while wiring Office UI.
- Bootstrap completed on 2026-04-26. Assistant identity is Chappie 🧠, Jarvis-like digital assistant: smart, thoughtful, calm, proactive. User is Темыч / Артём, timezone Moscow (UTC+3), prefers Russian, direct style, and wants an "AI office" that turns vague thoughts into plans/processes/artifacts.
- Google Calendar is connected via Composio and works from this environment. User’s primary calendar is a.sidnevart@gmail.com in Europe/Moscow.
- There is a likely Control UI bug/limitation on OpenClaw 2026.4.23: telegram:* sessions open in dashboard, but sending messages from dashboard into telegram sessions does not work reliably even when gateway auth is fixed. TUI/main/Telegram itself work; issue appears specific to dashboard send flow for telegram sessions.
- OpenClaw Office UI was already installed before changes. Final setup: systemd service `openclaw-office.service` on 127.0.0.1:5180, exposed through nginx at `https://80.74.25.43:8443/office/`, with websocket proxy working.
- For Office UI, gateway token should come from `/opt/openclaw-stack/secrets/gateway-token`; avoid exposing it in process argv or logs.
- Office UI package version in use is old enough that subpath support is not native; `/office/` works via nginx rewrites/sub_filter and may be somewhat fragile. Gateway/Telegram/Composio/web search were intentionally left untouched while wiring Office UI.
- Deployed a monitoring stack on 2026-04-26 under `/opt/openclaw-monitoring` using Docker Compose with `prometheus`, `grafana`, `node-exporter`, and `cadvisor`.
- Grafana is exposed only through nginx at `https://80.74.25.43:8443/grafana/`; internal monitoring ports are loopback-only: Grafana `127.0.0.1:3300`, Prometheus `127.0.0.1:9090`, node-exporter `127.0.0.1:9100`, cAdvisor `127.0.0.1:8083`.
- Monitoring includes a local OpenClaw exporter script at `/opt/openclaw-monitoring/scripts/openclaw_usage_exporter.py` writing Prometheus textfile metrics to `/var/lib/node_exporter/textfile_collector/openclaw.prom`, refreshed by `/etc/cron.d/openclaw-monitoring`.
- Grafana provisioning and dashboards live in `/opt/openclaw-monitoring/grafana/`; two dashboards were created and verified via Grafana API: `Server Overview` and `OpenClaw Usage Overview`.
- The monitoring stack README is at `/opt/openclaw-monitoring/README.md`; Grafana credentials are stored in `/opt/openclaw-monitoring/secrets/grafana.env` and should not be pasted into chat/logs.
